duct**: GPU - NVIDIA RTX 4070 Super  \n","- **Quantity Ordered**: 2  \n","- **Estimated Delivery**: In 5 days from the shipping date  \n","\n","Let me know if you want to change the quantity again or check anything else about this order.\n","----------------------------------------\n","USER : What about order MGR14S ?\n","\n","AGENT : Here are the details for order **MGR14S**:\n","\n","- **Product**: Monitor - 27in 1440p 165Hz  \n","- **Quantity Ordered**: 1  \n","- **Estimated Delivery**: In 5 days from the shipping date  \n","\n","If you’d like, I can update the quantity for this order as well.\n","----------------------------------------\n","USER : Bye\n","\n","AGENT : Goodbye! If you need to review or update any computer or parts orders in the future, just reach out.\n"]}],"source":["import os\n","\n","#Reuse the agents created in the previous chapters by importing their notebooks\n","#This will also import the chatbot and execute the code available.\n","#Ignore / hide the code output and use only the agents\n","\n","#import the Product QnA Agent\n","%run \"/content/drive/MyDrive/Group 3 - Agentic AI in Customer Service and Sales/(Agent 1) Product QnA Agentic chatbot.ipynb\"\n","print(\"===============================================================\")\n","#import the orders agents\n","%run \"/content/drive/MyDrive/Group 3 - Agentic AI in Customer Service and Sales/(Agent 2) Orders Chatbot with custom agent.ipynb\""]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":4,"id":"4afc6a85-8f73-4c0c-bac0-c6f24badbf30","metadata":{"id":"4afc6a85-8f73-4c0c-bac0-c6f24badbf30","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774388530926,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":4,"user":{"displayName":"Minh Khiet Le","userId":"01664335585798363567"}}},"outputs":[],"source":["import functools\n","# Helper function to invoke an agent\n","def agent_node(state, agent, name, config):\n","\n","    #extract thread-id from request for conversation memory\n","    #thread_id=config[\"metadata\"][\"thread_id\"]\n","    #Set the config for calling the agent\n","    #agent_config = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": thread_id}}\n","\n","    #Pass the thread-id to establish memory for chatbot\n","    #Invoke the agent with the state\n","    result = agent.invoke(state, config)\n","\n","    # Convert the agent output into a format that is suitable to append to the global state\n","    if isinstance(result, ToolMessage):\n","        pass\n","    else:\n","        final_result=AIMessage(result['messages'][-1].content)\n","    return {\n","        \"messages\": [final_result]\n","    }\n","\n","#Create the product QnA node\n","product_QnA_node=functools.partial(agent_node,\n","                                   agent=product_QnA_agent,\n","                                   name=\"Product_QnA_Agent\")\n","#Create the Orders node\n","#For a custom agent, the agent graph need to be provided as input\n","orders_node=functools.partial(agent_node,\n","                              agent=orders_agent.agent_graph,\n","                              name=\"Orders_Agent\")\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"97d925a9-4050-4de2-8dcb-bd9c044470fb","metadata":{"id":"97d925a9-4050-4de2-8dcb-bd9c044470fb"},"source":["## Create the Routing Agent & Chatbot\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":6,"id":"3d31b5b9-649d-4b6f-9480-b7754618eae4","metadata":{"id":"3d31b5b9-649d-4b6f-9480-b7754618eae4","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774388547173,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":58,"user":{"displayName":"Minh Khiet Le","userId":"01664335585798363567"}}},"outputs":[],"source":["#Creating the routing agent\n","\n","from typing import TypedDict, Annotated\n","from langgraph.graph import StateGraph, END\n","from langchain_core.messages import AnyMessage, SystemMessage, HumanMessage, ToolMessage\n","import operator\n","\n","class RouterAgentState(TypedDict):\n","    messages: Annotated[list[AnyMessage], operator.add]\n","\n","class RouterAgent:\n","\n","    def __init__(self, model, system_prompt, smalltalk_prompt, debug=False):\n","\n","        self.system_prompt=system_prompt\n","        self.smalltalk_prompt=smalltalk_prompt\n","        self.model=model\n","        self.debug=debug\n","\n","        router_graph=StateGraph(RouterAgentState)\n","        router_graph.add_node(\"Router\",self.call_llm)\n","        router_graph.add_node(\"Product_Agent\",product_QnA_node)\n","        router_graph.add_node(\"Orders_Agent\",orders_node)\n","        router_graph.add_node(\"Small_Talk\", self.respond_smalltalk)\n","\n","        router_graph.add_conditional_edges(\n","            \"Router\",\n","            self.find_route,\n","            {\"PRODUCT\": \"Product_Agent\",\n","             \"ORDER\" : \"Orders_Agent\",\n","             \"SMALLTALK\" : \"Small_Talk\",\n","             \"END\": END }\n","        )\n","\n","        #One way routing, not coming back to router\n","        router_graph.add_edge(\"Product_Agent\",END)\n","        router_graph.add_edge(\"Orders_Agent\",END)\n","        router_graph.add_edge(\"Small_Talk\",END)\n","\n","        #Set where there graph starts\n","        router_graph.set_entry_point(\"Router\")\n","        self.router_graph = router_graph.compile()\n","\n","    def call_llm(self, state:RouterAgentState):\n","        messages=state[\"messages\"]\n","        if self.debug:\n","            print(f\"Call LLM received {messages}\")\n","\n","        #If system prompt exists, add to messages in the front\n","        if self.system_prompt:\n","            messages = [SystemMessage(content=self.system_prompt)] + messages\n","\n","        #invoke the model with the message history\n","        result = self.model.invoke(messages)\n","\n","        if self.debug:\n","            print(f\"Call LLM result {result}\")\n","        return { \"messages\":[result] }\n","\n","    def respond_smalltalk(self, state:RouterAgentState):\n","        messages=state[\"messages\"]\n","        if self.debug:\n","            print(f\"Small talk received: {messages}\")\n","\n","        #If system prompt exists, add to messages in the front\n","\n","        messages = [SystemMessage(content=self.smalltalk_prompt)] + messages\n","\n","        #invoke the model with the message history\n","        result = self.model.invoke(messages)\n","\n","        if self.debug:\n","            print(f\"Small talk result {result}\")\n","        return { \"messages\":[result] }\n","\n","    def find_route(self, state:RouterAgentState):\n","        last_message = state[\"messages\"][-1]\n","        if self.debug:\n","            print(\"Router: Last result from LLM : \", last_message)\n","\n","        #Set the last message as the destination\n","        destination=last_message.content\n","\n","        if self.debug:\n","            print(f\"Destination chosen : {destination}\")\n","        return destination"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":8,"id":"2f9af521-affc-463d-927a-d0e09426f2e9","metadata":{"id":"2f9af521-affc-463d-927a-d0e09426f2e9","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":374},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774388614973,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":10821,"user":{"displayName":"Minh Khiet Le","userId":"01664335585798363567"}},"outputId":"db5f88bb-cbb1-4ae7-e781-42fec2b44429"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"image/png":"\n","text/plain":["<IPython.core.display.Image object>"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":8}],"source":["from IPython.display import Image\n","\n","#Setup the system problem\n","system_prompt = \"\"\"\n","You are a Router, that analyzes the input query and chooses 4 options:\n","SMALLTALK: If the user input is small talk, like greetings and good byes, or general questions that don't fit other categories.\n","PRODUCT: If the query is a product question about computer (pc) and pc parts, like features, specifications and pricing.\n","ORDER: If the query is about orders for (pc) and pc parts, like order status, order details or update order quantity\n","\n","The output should only be just one word out of the possible 4 : SMALLTALK, PRODUCT, ORDER, END.\n","\"\"\"\n","\n","smalltalk_prompt=\"\"\"\n","If the user request is small talk, like greetings and goodbyes, respond professionally.\n","Mention that you will be able to answer questions about (pc) and pc parts  features and provide order status and updates.\n","\"\"\"\n","\n","router_agent = RouterAgent(model,\n","                           system_prompt,\n","                           smalltalk_prompt,\n","                           debug=False)\n","\n","Image(router_agent.router_graph.get_graph().draw_mermaid_png())"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"aca8e58e-67eb-4bb0-ae26-d904290e59eb","metadata":{"id":"aca8e58e-67eb-4bb0-ae26-d904290e59eb"},"source":["## Execute the Routing chatbot"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":9,"id":"a55ad40f-912d-4e63-bd00-d2a017e9dfc5","metadata":{"collapsed":true,"id":"a55ad40f-912d-4e63-bd00-d2a017e9dfc5","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774388624064,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":4912,"user":{"displayName":"Minh Khiet Le","userId":"01664335585798363567"}},"outputId":"6c01d4b9-c0e4-4f49-f245-04dc693e68d7"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["================================ Human Message =================================\n","\n","Tell me about the features of RTX 4080\n","================================== Ai Message ==================================\n","\n","PRODUCT\n","================================== Ai Message ==================================\n","\n","Here’s what we have on the **NVIDIA RTX 4080** from our product data:\n","\n","- **Product type:** High‑end NVIDIA GeForce RTX 40‑series graphics card  \n","- **Design goal:**  \n","  - Built to significantly enhance overall **system performance**  \n","  - Aimed at demanding **applications**, **modern games**, and **heavy workloads**  \n","- **Use cases:**  \n","  - High‑resolution gaming  \n","  - Content creation (video editing, 3D, etc.)  \n","  - General performance‑focused desktop builds where GPU power is important  \n","\n","The internal description emphasizes it as a **reliable, performance‑oriented GPU** intended to improve system responsiveness and usability across a wide range of computing tasks.\n","\n","If you tell me how you plan to use it (4K gaming, VR, AI/ML, video editing, etc.), I can help you decide if the RTX 4080 is a good fit compared to other cards we carry.\n"]}],"source":["#Execute a single request\n","messages=[HumanMessage(content=\"Tell me about the features of RTX 4080\")]\n","result=router_agent.router_graph.invoke({\"messages\":messages},config)\n","for message in result['messages']:\n","    print(message.pretty_repr())"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":10,"id":"d1937615-0441-4ab8-8dae-46d39de88fbe","metadata":{"collapsed":true,"id":"d1937615-0441-4ab8-8dae-46d39de88fbe","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774388631177,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":3307,"user":{"displayName":"Minh Khiet Le","userId":"01664335585798363567"}},"outputId":"2d7e9f11-fc5b-477d-d77f-d7732b53e11e"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["================================ Human Message =================================\n","\n","What is the status of order 9V81KQ?\n","================================== Ai Message ==================================\n","\n","ORDER\n","================================== Ai Message ==================================\n","\n","Here’s the status for order **9V81KQ**:\n","\n","- **Item:** Monitor - 27\" 1440p 165Hz  \n","- **Quantity:** 2 units  \n","- **Estimated delivery:** **within 5 days** from the shipping date\n","\n","If you tell me when it was shipped (or when you placed the order if you don’t know the ship date), I can give you a more specific expected delivery date.\n"]}],"source":["#Execute a single request\n","messages=[HumanMessage(content=\"What is the status of order 9V81KQ?\")]\n","result=router_agent.router_graph.invoke({\"messages\":messages},config)\n","for message in result['messages']:\n","    print(message.pretty_repr())"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## RUN THE Agent Bot and chat with it here\n"],"metadata":{"id":"yW49UIFGr2vG"},"id":"yW49UIFGr2vG"},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":11,"id":"D7K9_fPB_1rA","metadata":{"collapsed":true,"id":"D7K9_fPB_1rA","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774388875938,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":242707,"user":{"displayName":"Minh Khiet Le","userId":"01664335585798363567"}},"outputId":"49c0765c-2e6a-4254-92f9-45105d67da36"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["USER : hi\n","----------------------------------------\n","AGENT : Hello! How can I help you today?\n","\n","I can answer questions about PCs and PC parts (like CPUs, GPUs, RAM, storage, etc.), help you compare features or choose components, and I can also provide order status and updates if you share your order details.\n","USER : Can you show me the list of product I should get for high end gaming? \n","----------------------------------------\n","AGENT : Here’s a solid high‑end gaming build list using products we carry, based on the catalog results:\n","\n","**CPU (Processor) – choose one high-end option**\n","- Intel Core i9-13900K  \n","- AMD Ryzen 9 7950X  \n","- (Alternative slightly lower tier: AMD Ryzen 9 5900X, Intel Core i7-12700K, AMD Ryzen 5 7600)\n","\n","**GPU (Graphics Card) – for high-end gaming**\n","- NVIDIA RTX 4080  \n","- AMD RX 7800 XT  \n","- (Alternative: AMD RX 6800)\n","\n","**Motherboard – match to your CPU platform**\n","- For Intel 12th/13th Gen: ASUS TUF Gaming B650-PLUS (AMD board) is listed, but for AMD AM5 CPUs like Ryzen 9 7950X / Ryzen 5 7600  \n","- For AMD AM4: Gigabyte B550 AORUS Elite  \n","- (If you go Ryzen 9 7950X or Ryzen 5 7600 → ASUS TUF Gaming B650-PLUS is the right class of board)\n","\n","**Memory (RAM)**\n","- High-end DDR5: Corsair Vengeance 32GB DDR5 6000 (ideal for AM5 / newer Intel)  \n","- DDR4 option: G.Skill Trident Z 16GB DDR4 3600 (you may want 32GB for truly high-end)\n","\n","**Storage**\n","- Primary fast SSD: Samsung 980 PRO 2TB NVMe  \n","- Additional mass storage: Seagate Barracuda 2TB HDD\n","\n","**Power Supply (PSU)**\n","- Corsair RM850x 850W  \n","- EVGA SuperNOVA 750 G5 (850W is safer for RTX 4080-class builds; 750W is fine for slightly lower GPUs)\n","\n","**Case**\n","- Lian Li PC-O11 Dynamic  \n","- Corsair 4000D Airflow  \n","- NZXT H510  \n","\n","**CPU Cooling**\n","- NZXT Kraken X63 (AIO liquid cooler)  \n","- Noctua NH-D15 (top-tier air cooler)  \n","- Cooler Master Hyper 212 (more mid-range, but listed)\n","\n","---\n","\n","If you tell me:\n","- Which CPU brand you prefer (Intel vs AMD),\n","- Your resolution/refresh target (1080p/144Hz, 1440p/165Hz, 4K/120Hz),\n","- Your approximate budget,\n","\n","I can turn this into one or two *exact* recommended part lists (every component matched and compatible).\n","USER : turn into 1 exact pc part for each part\n","----------------------------------------\n","AGENT : I’m not sure what you want changed into “1 exact pc part for each part.”\n","\n","Please clarify one of these so I can help:\n","\n","- Do you have a **list of parts** you want cleaned up so that each line is a single, exact PC part (e.g., turn “Intel i7 or Ryzen 7 CPU” into one specific model each)?\n","- Do you want me to **design a full PC build** with exactly one specific part for each category (CPU, GPU, RAM, etc.)?\n","- Or do you want to **convert a messy parts list** (like from a screenshot or text) into a structured list with one precise item per line?\n","\n","Paste the list or describe what you’re trying to do (and your budget / use case if it’s a build), and I’ll turn it into one exact PC part per category.\n","USER : I want to build 6000$ pc \n","----------------------------------------\n","AGENT : To design a $6000 PC, I need a bit more information from you so I can tailor the build properly:\n","\n","1) What is the main use?\n","- High-end 4K gaming\n","- Streaming + gaming\n","- Video editing / 3D rendering / AI work\n","- Mixed (gaming + productivity)\n","\n","2) Do you need any of these included in the $6000 budget?\n","- Monitor\n","- Keyboard / mouse\n","- Speakers / headset\n","- Windows license\n","\n","3) Any brand preferences?\n","- Intel or AMD for CPU?\n","- NVIDIA or AMD for GPU?\n","- Case style: glass RGB showcase vs simple/quiet\n","\n","Once you answer those, I’ll put together a full parts list that fits close to $6000 using components we carry (CPU, GPU, motherboard, RAM, storage, PSU, case, cooler, etc.) and can adjust if you want to prioritize either max gaming FPS or workstation performance.\n","USER : High end 4k gaming, include everything in 6000$ budget range, mainly AMD and NDVIA, Fish tank cass with fancy rbg \n","----------------------------------------\n","AGENT : Here’s a high‑end 4K gaming setup in your ~$6000 budget, focused on AMD CPU + NVIDIA GPU, with a “fish tank”‑style showcase case and strong RGB.\n","\n","Because the store catalog doesn’t show a dedicated aquarium/fish‑tank case model, I’ll base the build around the **Lian Li PC‑O11 Dynamic**, which is the closest: a glass showcase case that’s very popular for custom water/fish‑tank style builds and heavy RGB.\n","\n","---\n","\n","## Core PC (High‑End 4K Gaming)\n","\n","**Case (showcase / “fish tank” style with RGB):**  \n","- **Lian Li PC‑O11 Dynamic**  \n","  - Panoramic tempered glass, perfect for a “fish tank” aesthetic with visible components and RGB.\n","\n","**CPU (AMD):**  \n","- **AMD Ryzen 9 7950X**  \n","  - 16 cores / 32 threads, excellent for high‑end gaming, streaming, and content creation.\n","\n","**Motherboard (AM5):**  \n","- **ASUS TUF Gaming B650‑PLUS**  \n","  - Stable power delivery, good VRMs, PCIe 4.0, and plenty of connectivity for a high‑end build.\n","\n","**CPU Cooler (high‑end air or AIO):**  \n","Choose one style:\n","- **Noctua NH‑D15** – top‑tier air cooling, extremely reliable  \n","  or  \n","- **Corsair H100i 240mm AIO** – if you prefer RGB liquid cooling look\n","\n","**Graphics Card (NVIDIA for 4K):**  \n","- **NVIDIA RTX 4080**  \n","  - Excellent for high‑refresh 4K gaming with ray tracing and DLSS.  \n","  - Sits comfortably in a $6000 full‑setup budget with room for premium peripherals.\n","\n","**Memory (RGB capable):**  \n","- **Corsair Vengeance 32GB DDR5 6000** (2×16GB)  \n","  - Fast DDR5, ideal capacity for 4K gaming and multitasking.\n","\n","**Storage:**  \n","- **Samsung 980 PRO 2TB NVMe SSD** – main drive for OS and games  \n","- (Optional) **Seagate Barracuda 2TB HDD** – for mass storage if you need extra space\n","\n","**Power Supply:**  \n","- **Corsair RM850x 850W** or **EVGA SuperNOVA 850 G6**  \n","  - 850W is plenty for a Ryzen 9 + RTX 4080 system with overhead.\n","\n","---\n","\n","## 4K Monitor (Gaming)\n","\n","From our catalog, we don’t have specific model names listed for monitors, but for your budget and GPU:\n","\n","- Look for a **27\"–32\" 4K monitor** with:\n","  - **144Hz or higher refresh rate**\n","  - **G‑SYNC Compatible / Adaptive Sync**\n","  - IPS or fast VA panel\n","\n","This will pair well with the RTX 4080 for high‑FPS 4K gaming.\n","\n","---\n","\n","## Peripherals (RGB / Gaming)\n","\n","The catalog doesn’t list specific keyboard/mouse/headset models by name, but here’s what fits your brief and budget:\n","\n","- **Mechanical RGB Gaming Keyboard**  \n","  - Full‑size, per‑key RGB, linear or tactile switches based on your preference.\n","\n","- **RGB Gaming Mouse**  \n","  - Adjustable DPI (up to 12K+), side buttons, RGB lighting.\n","\n","- **RGB Mousepad (optional)**  \n","  - Extended pad with RGB edge lighting to match the “fancy RGB” theme.\n","\n","- **Gaming Headset**  \n","  - 7.1 surround or virtual surround, good mic, comfortable for long sessions, ideally with RGB to match the rest of the setup.\n","\n","---\n","\n","## How This Fits a ~$6000 Budget\n","\n","This kind of configuration (Ryzen 9 7950X + RTX 4080 + 32GB DDR5 + 2TB NVMe + showcase case + 4K high‑refresh monitor + premium RGB peripherals) is appropriate for a **complete** ~$6000 build including:\n","\n","- Tower and all internal components  \n","- High‑end 4K gaming monitor  \n","- RGB keyboard, mouse, mousepad, headset\n","\n","Exact total depends on current prices, but you’ll be well within your range with some headroom for extra RGB fans, custom cables, or aesthetic upgrades.\n","\n","---\n","\n","If you’d like, I can next:\n","- Break this into a line‑item quote and swap parts to lean more towards aesthetics (more RGB, custom fans) or  \n","- Tune it more for productivity (more storage, more RAM) while staying in budget.\n","USER : What is the total cost? \n","----------------------------------------\n","AGENT : To calculate the total cost, I’ll need your order ID so I can look up the order details and pricing.\n","\n","Please provide:\n","- Your order ID (exactly as shown in your confirmation/email).\n","USER : I haven't order, can you tell me the total for the list of the part? \n","----------------------------------------\n","AGENT : Sure, I can help with that.  \n","\n","Please provide the list of PC parts (names/models) you’re considering, and I’ll look up each item and calculate the total price for you.\n","USER : **Case (showcase / “fish tank” style with RGB):**   - **Lian Li PC‑O11 Dynamic**     - Panoramic tempered glass, perfect for a “fish tank” aesthetic with visible components and RGB.  **CPU (AMD):**   - **AMD Ryzen 9 7950X**     - 16 cores / 32 threads, excellent for high‑end gaming, streaming, and content creation.  **Motherboard (AM5):**   - **ASUS TUF Gaming B650‑PLUS**     - Stable power delivery, good VRMs, PCIe 4.0, and plenty of connectivity for a high‑end build.  **CPU Cooler (high‑end air or AIO):**   Choose one style: - 